HB193 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2 Relating to Marshall County; to amend Section
3 45-48-111.03, Code of Alabama 1975; to require that the
4 presiding circuit judge, circuit clerk, and presiding district
5 judge are part of the committee to select the custodian of
6 voting tabulators; to clarify custodian responsibilities; and
7 to increase the custodian's salary.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
9 Section 1. Section 45-48-111.03, Code of Alabama 1975,
10 is amended to read as follows:
11 "§45-48-111.03
12 (a) A custodian of voting machinestabulators shall be
13 appointed by a committee composed of the seniorpresiding
14 circuit judge, who shall also be the chair, the judge of
15 probate, tax collectorcircuit clerk, sheriff, and the county
16 judgepresiding district judge. SuchThe custodian of voting
17 machinestabulators shall have attended a recognized school
18 that teaches thetraining course that teaches operation and
19 handling of voting machinestabulators, or in lieu thereof must
20 have had at least three years' experience in the operation and
21 handling of voting machinestabulators.
22 (b) The custodian shall be responsible for performing
23 all duties as set out in Section 17-9-28necessary, or
24 incidental, to maintaining the county voting tabulators
25 including, but not limited to, the following:
26 (1) Testing all voting tabulators and comparing the
27 test results to the manufacturer's specifications ensuring a
28 perfect match.
Page 1

perfect match.
HB193 Enrolled
29 (2) Installing new paper rolls in all tabulators.
30 (3) Clearing any testing totals.
31 (4) Sealing voting tabulator units for delivery to the
32 voting precincts.
33 (5) Testing all equipment for use by individuals under
34 the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) to ensure they are
35 working properly.
36 (6) Conducting a public test of the voting tabulators
37 as scheduled by the judge of probate.
38 (7) Resealing all public test units for delivery to the
39 voting precincts.
40 (8) Overseeing the delivery of equipment to the polling
41 precincts.
42 (9) Supporting the voting tabulators and ADA equipment
43 on election day.
44 (10) Overseeing the pickup of all voting tabulators and
45 ADA equipment and securing the tabulators and equipment at the
46 Marshall County Elections Warehouse.
47 (11) Charging voting equipment if required to ensure
48 that the machines are operational on election day.
49 (12) Testing all equipment for any recounts and
50 attending the recounts.
51 (c) The custodian of voting machinestabulators shall
52 receive a salary in the amount of eight thousand nine hundred
53 dollars ($8,900)twenty-seven thousand dollars ($27,000) per
54 annum payable in equal monthly installments, effective upon
55 July 1, 2026. The Marshall County Commission, by resolution
56 adopted in a duly called meeting of the Marshall County
Page 2

adopted in a duly called meeting of the Marshall County
HB193 Enrolled
57 Commission, may provide for increases in the salary of the
58 custodian of voting tabulators beginning on June 1, 2028. The
59 salary shall be paid from the general fund of the county. and
60 before entering uponBefore beginning his or her duties, the
61 custodian shall be bonded in the sum of ten twenty thousand
62 dollars ($10,000)($20,000) for the faithful performance of his
63 or her duties as are other public officials."
64 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
65 2026.
